javacsw.services.cs

Interface IConfigManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JConfigManager, JConfigServiceClient

    public interface IConfigManager
    Defines an asynchronous (non-blocking) java interface for storing and retrieving configuration information

      • get

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.util.Optional<IConfigData>> get(java.io.File path,
                                                                            java.util.Date date)
        Gets the file as it existed on the given date. If date is before the file was created, the initial version is returned. If date is after the last change, the most recent version is returned. If the path does not exist in the repo, an empty value is returned.
        Parameters:
        path - the file path relative to the repository root
        date - the target date
        Returns:
        a future object that can be used to access the file's data, if found
